eNCA's Ayesha Ismail reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Western Cape rural areas lack the means to register their elderly for the COVID-19 vaccine. The health department is turning its focus to them and has trained dozens of its employees to help in these communities. READ: Race to register the elderly for COVID-19 vaccine There are also 75 Cape Access eCentres across the province with free internet. The Western Cape's head of health, Keith Cloete said the province will make equal access a priority. Watch the video above for more details on this story.